2500|$|Let us suppose {{now that}} {{there is at least}} a {{positive}} solution, and let [...] be the minimal one. In addition, let us suppose that the sphere is the nearest object on our scene intersecting our ray, and that it is made of a reflective material. We need to find in which direction the light ray is reflected. The laws of reflection state that the angle of reflection is equal and opposite to the angle of incidence between the <b>incident</b> <b>ray</b> and the normal to the sphere.|$|E
