5000|$|The [...] or {{transmitted}} ray {{corresponding to}} a given <b>incident</b> <b>ray</b> represents the light that is transmitted through the surface. The angle between this ray and the normal {{is known as the}} angle of refraction, and it is given by Snell's Law. Conservation of energy requires that the power in the <b>incident</b> <b>ray</b> must equal the sum of the power in the refracted ray, the power in the reflected ray, and any power absorbed at the surface.|$|E
