50|$|A major {{challenge}} {{that must be}} addressed in any solar concentrating technology is the changing angle of the <b>incident</b> <b>rays</b> (the rays of sunlight striking the mirrors) as the sun progresses throughout the day. The reflectors of a CLFR are typically aligned in a north-south orientation and turn about a single axis using a computer controlled solar tracker system. This allows the system to maintain the proper angle of incidence between the sun’s rays and the mirrors, thereby optimizing energy transfer.|$|R
